In addition, the text made it clear that the restrictions on the holding of certain posts for foreigners would not apply to those who had in writing renounced “other” citizenship and had handed over the previous passport to the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs, but had not ceased to be a national of another country “for reasons beyond its control”.
It is now prohibited for foreigners to hold positions in the municipal service, to be employed in facilities and in organizations whose activities are linked to the security of Russia.
Also, a person with a dual nationality or a residence permit in another country may not become a member of the State Duma or a member of the Federation Council.
The law was scheduled to enter into force on 1 September 2017, and the necessary by-laws should be in place by that time.
